{
  "abstract": "Groundnut (Arachis hypogaea L.) is an annual legume, grown\r\nprimarily for high quality edible oil and easily digestible protein\r\nin its seeds. It is cultivated in 109 countries, in tropical, subtropical,\r\nand warm temperate regions of the world. In India during\r\n2010-11 it was grown on 4.93 million ha with an estimated total\r\nproduction of 5.64 million tonnes (groundnuts in shell) and an\r\naverage productivity of 1144 kg/ ha (FAO 2011)...",
